profile_positions.description:
PUM Netherlands Senior Experts is the largest European non-profit (and mainly Dutch government funded) organization advising businesses in developing countries and emerging markets for over 40 years. It was founded by the Dutch Ministry of Foreign Affairs and the Employers Association VNO-NCW.
Its vision is a world in which entrepreneurship drives sustainable development. Vibrant businesses, better lives. 

For Netherlands Senior Experts I have done (renewable) energy network projects in developing countries, projects that needed a combination of subject-matter and commercial expertise: 
. India (Tamil Nadu IPP offshore wind project and feed-in contract; (2) Gujarat, Little Rann of Kutch, local onshore wind projects); 
. South-Africa (production of thermal solar heater systems, strategic reorientation and business process redesign of maintenance dept., and (2) coaching of the general manager); 
. Philippines (rural electrification; development and improvement of HV network on Mindanao island; development of wind, biomass and small hydro plants); 
. Jordan (solar PV and wind IPP tender projects, power purchase agreements); 
. Tanzania (marketing of liquid gases; rural electrification and clean solar cooking solutions); 
. Mali (FRES rural electrification: operations/ financial management of solar PV systems for off-grid remote areas: developed a standard operations manual to be used in other African countries); 
. Morocco (marketing off-grid solar, PV/thermal, and solar PV irrigation/pumping systems); 
. Senegal (off-grid solar for rural electrification, international partnership, feed-in contracts); 
. Kazakhstan (improve strategy, operations of an energy and mining engineering consultancy).
. Honduras (energy saving and PV/thermal solar energy project, developed PV power plant for hotel resort - ecotourism).
. Rwanda (feasibility of a small hydro power installation).
. South Africa (feasibility of small hydro for a diary farm, a citrus farm and a macadamia farm).
